Why?

1482
00:52:40,380 --> 00:52:43,200
Because it's gotten itself stretched out so much

1483
00:52:43,200 --> 00:52:44,440
that this is unimportant.

1484
00:52:44,880 --> 00:52:46,340
Let's assume that's unimportant.

1485
00:52:48,660 --> 00:52:49,440
All right,

1486
00:52:49,440 --> 00:52:50,560
this is the potential energy.

1487
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:54,360
This looks like a kinetic energy of something.

1488
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:56,100
It's not a kinetic energy of something.

1489
00:52:56,100 --> 00:52:57,620
It's not the motion of a particle,

1490
00:52:58,400 --> 00:52:59,440
but mathematically,

1491
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:03,120
it's proportional to the square of a time derivative.

1492
00:53:03,320 --> 00:53:04,760
It looks like a kinetic energy

1493
00:53:04,760 --> 00:53:07,040
of a degree of freedom,

1494
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:08,700
which in this case is a field,

1495
00:53:08,860 --> 00:53:10,720
and this looks like a potential energy.

1496
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:13,040
What would be the Lagrangian?

1497
00:53:13,080 --> 00:53:14,200
This would be the energy.

1498
00:53:14,360 --> 00:53:16,800
What would be the Lagrangian of such a thing?

1499
00:53:20,380 --> 00:53:22,160
Energy is T plus V.

1500
00:53:22,960 --> 00:53:24,500
Lagrangian is T minus V.

1501
00:53:24,500 --> 00:53:26,440
T stands for kinetic energy.

1502
00:53:27,220 --> 00:53:28,780
So the Lagrangian...

1503
00:53:30,980 --> 00:53:33,060
So the Lagrangian is T minus V.

1504
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:34,840
Now,

1505
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:35,360
actually,

1506
00:53:35,360 --> 00:53:36,800
this is not the Lagrangian.

1507
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:38,460
This is the Lagrange density.

1508
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:42,320
You have to multiply it by the volume of space.

1509
00:53:42,920 --> 00:53:44,840
This was not the potential energy.

1510
00:53:44,960 --> 00:53:46,860
This was the potential energy density.

1511
00:53:47,700 --> 00:53:49,240
To get the potential energy,

1512
00:53:49,420 --> 00:53:51,480
you have to multiply it by the volume of space,

1513
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:52,040
right?

1514
00:53:52,460 --> 00:53:53,300
Same here.

1515
00:53:53,300 --> 00:53:54,580
This was energy density.

1516
00:53:55,140 --> 00:53:59,800
So what's the volume of space?

1517
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:01,560
Well,

1518
00:54:01,560 --> 00:54:02,940
A cubed.

1519
00:54:06,500 --> 00:54:08,140
A cubed of time.

1520
00:54:08,940 --> 00:54:09,820
So now,

1521
00:54:09,820 --> 00:54:12,660
if we know how A cubed behaves with time,

1522
00:54:12,840 --> 00:54:15,820
we have the Lagrangian of this field,

1523
00:54:15,820 --> 00:54:16,520
phi.

1524
00:54:17,380 --> 00:54:17,940
Okay,

